# {{PROJECT_NAME}}

This repository is the **operating layer** for the {{PROJECT_NAME}} research project: a shared knowledge base and rule set that lets Claude act as a consistent research collaborator (the {{ROLE_TERM}}) across Claude Chat and Claude Code. It was generated from the [ResearchPartner](https://github.com/koba-jon/ResearchPartner) base template.

## How it is used

- **Claude Chat (Project):** paste `project-instructions.txt` into the Project's custom instructions. The {{ROLE_TERM}} then reads `docs/entrypoint.md` first each session and pulls only the docs it needs.
- **Claude Code:** prompts follow `docs/operations/prompt-factory.md` and the path variables in `docs/entrypoint.md` section 0.
- **Keeping Chat in sync:** the Project reads a snapshot of this repo. After Claude Code pushes (or you push), refresh the Project's connected source so the {{ROLE_TERM}} reads the latest commit, not a stale copy.
- **Knowledge base:** everything the project knows lives under `docs/` and is the single source of truth, gated by `make docs-check`.

## Layout

- `docs/` — the knowledge base (start at `docs/entrypoint.md`).
- `scripts/` — the framework engine, the consistency guard, and the lifecycle tools.
- `ownership.json` — which files the framework re-renders vs which you own.
- `researchpartner.config.json` — this clone's configuration.
<!-- if:SRC_MIRROR_ENABLED=yes -->- `src/` — a read-only mirror of your project source (run `make sync-src`).<!-- endif -->
